sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS Terminate
    participant Authorino as Kuadrant Authorino<br/>5001/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant BBR as payload-processing (BBR)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Limitador as Kuadrant Limitador<br/>8081/TCP gRPC mTLS
    participant KServe as KServe Model Pod<br/>8000/TCP HTTPS
    participant ExtProvider as External Provider<br/>(OpenAI/Anthropic)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,KServe: Flow 1: Internal Model Inference (LLMInferenceService)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (API key or OpenShift token)
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation<br/>gRPC/mTLS (Istio)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>HTTP (NetworkPolicy restricted)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Key validation result (SHA-256 hash check)
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>HTTP (NetworkPolicy restricted)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Selected subscription + headers
        Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc: extract model name<br/>gRPC/TLS (DestinationRule SIMPLE)
        BBR-->>Gateway: X-Gateway-Model-Name header
        Gateway->>Limitador: TokenRateLimitPolicy evaluation<br/>gRPC/mTLS (Istio)
        Limitador-->>Gateway: Rate limit decision
        Gateway->>KServe: Forward to model pod (via HTTPRoute)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (cluster-internal)
        KServe-->>Gateway: Inference response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON response<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over Client,ExtProvider: Flow 2: External Model Inference (ExternalModel)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation<br/>gRPC/mTLS
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: Validate + select subscription
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription + identity headers
        Gateway->>BBR: ext_proc: model extraction + provider resolution<br/>+ API translation + credential injection
        BBR-->>Gateway: Transformed request + injected API key
        Gateway->>Limitador: TokenRateLimitPolicy evaluation
        Limitador-->>Gateway: Rate limit decision
        Gateway->>ExtProvider: Forward to external provider<br/>HTTPS/TLS 1.2+ (Istio origination)<br/>Auth: Injected API key from credentialRef Secret
        ExtProvider-->>Gateway: Provider response
        Gateway-->>Client: Translated response<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    end

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: API Key Creation
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OpenShift or existing API key)
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
        Authorino-->>Gateway: X-MaaS-Username, X-MaaS-Group headers
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: Forward (via HTTPRoute)<br/>HTTP (cluster-internal)
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Store key hash (SHA-256 with key_id salt)<br/>TCP/5432
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Stored
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: sk-oai-{key_id}_{secret} (show-once)
        Gateway-->>Client: API key response<br/>HTTPS/TLS
    end

    rect rgb(243, 229, 245)
        Note over Client,KServe: Flow 4: Model Discovery (/v1/models)
        Client->>Gateway: GET /v1/models<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: Forward (via HTTPRoute)
        MaaSAPI->>MaaSAPI: MaaSModelRef list from informer cache
        MaaSAPI->>KServe: HTTP probe /v1/models per model<br/>HTTPS/8000 (InsecureSkipVerify)
        KServe-->>MaaSAPI: Model availability
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: OpenAI-compatible model list<br/>Cache-Control: no-store
        Gateway-->>Client: Model list response
    end
